WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:02.991
Ralph Angel:
Previously on
"Queen Sugar"...

00:03.040 --> 00:05.474
The Landrys have the power
and the influence.

00:05.520 --> 00:08.216
That time is coming
to an end.

00:08.260 --> 00:11.002
They're trying
to intimidate us,

00:11.050 --> 00:14.178
but these black bodies...
are real.

00:14.230 --> 00:16.004
It's important
that I'm in his life.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.790
- His father.
- You ain't shit, Davis.
You know that?

00:17.840 --> 00:19.796
- I want joint custody.
- No.

00:19.840 --> 00:22.058
I'm tired of going to Charley
every time I need something.

00:22.100 --> 00:24.182
Pops wanted me
to keep farming,

00:24.240 --> 00:25.582
and that's
what I wanna do.

00:25.630 --> 00:27.063
What did they say,
Roberta?

00:27.110 --> 00:29.499
That rig Hollywood's on
just had an explosion.

00:31.240 --> 00:34.243
[Violet laughs ]

00:34.290 --> 00:37.339
_ _ All these
JUICY berries need
is some chocolate.

00:37.380 --> 00:39.245
Aw, wait till you see
what I got.

00:39.300 --> 00:41.029
[ music playing
on radio ]

00:41.080 --> 00:43.162
Bam!
What about this?

00:43.210 --> 00:45.599
Oh!
Well, that'll do
just fine, baby.

00:45.650 --> 00:48.608
Besides, you can't handle
the chocolate you got.

00:48.650 --> 00:50.208
What you talking about?

00:50.260 --> 00:53.434
I'm talking about you.
Baby, you still got it.

00:53.480 --> 00:55.436
I'm just saying you might be
a little bit out of practice.

00:55.490 --> 00:56.912
Me?

00:56.960 --> 00:58.393
[laughs]

00:58.440 --> 01:00.135
You the one
breathing hard.

01:00.190 --> 01:01.487
Mm-hmm.

01:01.530 --> 01:03.919
Acting like you on
your way to glory.

01:03.970 --> 01:05.016
[laughs]

01:05.060 --> 01:08.109
You know it takes
two to tango.

01:08.150 --> 01:09.845
All I'm saying is...

01:11.460 --> 01:13.109
[ giggling ]

01:13.160 --> 01:16.414
One day away from you
is one day too long.

01:20.160 --> 01:21.946
Baby”.

01:21.990 --> 01:24.948
don't give up
on us again.

01:24.990 --> 01:27.163
I need you, chre.

01:30.430 --> 01:33.388
- Where you going?
- I am a lady.

01:33.440 --> 01:36.261
And it is time for me
to do my lady things.

01:36.310 --> 01:38.392
Then I'm coming back.

01:38.440 --> 01:40.135
And when I do,

01:40.180 --> 01:43.445
I do not intend
to be a lady.

01:43.490 --> 01:45.139
Understood?

01:45.190 --> 01:46.441
I understand.

01:54.670 --> 01:57.230
[ theme music playing ]

01:57.290 --> 01:58.848
Dreams never die

01:58.900 --> 02:01.152
Take flight
as the world turns

02:01.200 --> 02:02.804
Dreams never die

02:02.860 --> 02:04.942
Take flight
as the world turns

02:04.990 --> 02:07.458
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight

02:09.520 --> 02:11.078
Dreams never die

02:16.780 --> 02:20.864
Keep the colors
in the lines

02:20.920 --> 02:24.651
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight.

02:24.700 --> 02:27.874
- [ sizzling ]
- This stuff'll be
ready in a minute.

02:27.930 --> 02:29.443
Sure you don't want
something hot?

02:30.580 --> 02:32.184
Stick to them ribs.

02:32.230 --> 02:35.791
Thanks.
Just gonna inhale this.

02:35.850 --> 02:38.193
Get some rest
before I have to leave.

02:41.630 --> 02:43.188
I feel you.

02:43.250 --> 02:44.672
You know that, right?

02:45.900 --> 02:48.414
I do, but...

02:48.470 --> 02:51.166
- I'm okay, so...
- And I know you don't want
to hear this right now...

02:52.340 --> 02:54.205
but remaining silent

02:54.260 --> 02:55.943
when one must speak...

02:58.610 --> 03:01.647
is the slow death
of freedom.

03:01.700 --> 03:03.600
I want you to be free.

03:10.710 --> 03:12.052
Um...

03:15.840 --> 03:17.626
I'm just tired.

03:25.500 --> 03:26.933
[ doorbell rings ]

03:28.510 --> 03:30.978
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:31.030 --> 03:33.078
How is he?

03:33.120 --> 03:35.907
He's okay.
He's good.

03:35.950 --> 03:38.168
Been sleeping a lot.

03:38.210 --> 03:39.768
I guess that's
to be expected.

03:39.820 --> 03:41.959
Well, I think there's
more to it than that.

03:44.740 --> 03:46.822
Charley:
Where you going?

03:46.870 --> 03:48.303
I got invited
to a symposium

03:48.350 --> 03:50.523
on mass incarceration
In Atlanta,

03:50.570 --> 03:52.049
sponsored by the NABJ.

03:52.100 --> 03:54.318
Well, that's great!
Congratulations.

03:54.360 --> 03:56.316
Thanks.
I'm looking forward to it.

03:56.360 --> 03:58.146
Hmm.

03:58.190 --> 03:59.407
About Micah...

04:01.320 --> 04:03.231
I'm worried about him.

04:03.280 --> 04:05.328
I know.

04:05.370 --> 04:06.974
I am, too.

04:07.020 --> 04:08.931
I just think
he needs some time.

04:08.980 --> 04:10.800
He's not eating.

04:10.850 --> 04:12.499
He's not talking.

04:12.550 --> 04:15.724
He slept the whole time
he's been here.

04:15.770 --> 04:18.238
And you know Micah wet himself
the night the police took him?

04:20.820 --> 04:22.299
[ cell phone ringing ]

04:27.310 --> 04:29.528
- [ cell phone beeps ]
- Hey, Rah.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.731
Nah, I-I didn't
mention it yet.

04:31.790 --> 04:34.224
But she over here right now
if you wanna get at her.

04:35.790 --> 04:37.439
Rah needs to talk to you.

04:37.490 --> 04:40.050
Hey, Ralph Angel.
Need something?

04:40.100 --> 04:42.227
I already talked to Nova,
and she cool with it.

04:42.280 --> 04:44.794
Look, FSA got a program.

04:44.840 --> 04:47.274
Now I can get that loan,
plant them cover crops.

04:47.330 --> 04:49.548
The cover crops
we didn't agree to.

04:49.590 --> 04:51.808
Am I running
this farm or not?

04:51.850 --> 04:54.546
Day to day,
but the big decisions,
we're still needing to--

04:54.590 --> 04:56.933
They gonna let me put up
my part of the farm
for collateral.

04:56.990 --> 04:59.413
We just convinced a bunch
of sugarcane farmers

04:59.470 --> 05:01.688
to take a chance
and grind With us.

05:01.730 --> 05:03.903
How's it gonna look
that we're using
part of our land

05:03.950 --> 05:04.905
as a side hustle?

05:04.950 --> 05:06.736
[ car door opens ]

05:06.780 --> 05:09.385
Ralph Angel:
My parole officer here.
I gotta go.

05:09.430 --> 05:11.478
- Kevin: What's up,
little man?
- Blue: Hey.

05:11.520 --> 05:13.693
Give me a low five.
There you go.

05:13.740 --> 05:15.264
- [ door opens ]
- Your daddy home?

05:15.310 --> 05:17.039
- What's going on?
- Man.

05:17.090 --> 05:18.694
- Good morning.
- What's up?

05:18.750 --> 05:20.741
- You good, Blue?
- I'm awesome.

05:20.790 --> 05:24.749
All right, awesome.
Awesome. Cool.

05:24.800 --> 05:26.358
Zoom!

05:26.410 --> 05:28.753
[ music playing
on car stereo ]

05:28.800 --> 05:30.358
You sleep okay?

05:30.410 --> 05:31.581
Mm-hmm.

05:37.420 --> 05:38.978
You wanna talk?

05:39.030 --> 05:40.930
- About what?
- How you're doing.

05:44.210 --> 05:47.202
You went through something,
and-- and it's okay--

05:47.250 --> 05:48.592
Mom, I'm good.

05:53.480 --> 05:55.254
So, you're divorced now.

05:58.570 --> 06:01.391
No, not yet.

06:01.440 --> 06:03.522
I'm sorry, babe.
I know this is hard on you.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.263
So you're, like,
fighting over money.

06:05.320 --> 06:06.833
No, we're arguing over you.

06:13.980 --> 06:16.494
Did you tell your father
that you wanted him

06:16.550 --> 06:18.063
to have shared custody?

06:18.110 --> 06:21.500
Yeah, I mean,
I did tell him
I wanna see him

06:21.550 --> 06:23.029
more than I have
the last few months.

06:23.070 --> 06:25.288
But did you say
you wanted him

06:25.340 --> 06:28.298
to have legal
shared custody?

06:37.570 --> 06:39.697
That's what I thought.

06:39.740 --> 06:42.300
You're the only person
I know to ask

06:42.350 --> 06:44.352
that don't know
my whole family.

06:44.400 --> 06:46.834
It's okay
that it's handwritten?

06:46.880 --> 06:48.393
Um...

06:51.670 --> 06:53.570
[ chuckles ]
Wow.

06:56.850 --> 06:58.624
Good for you,
Ralph Angel.

07:00.940 --> 07:03.545
- This is incredible, man.
- I know, right?

07:03.590 --> 07:04.761
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

07:06.380 --> 07:08.245
- [ sighs ]
- Well, it's signed,

07:08.290 --> 07:11.418
it's partially dated,
but the intent is clear.

07:11.470 --> 07:13.028
- Mm-hmm.
- I mean, I'm no lawyer,

07:13.080 --> 07:15.298
but it should stand up
in court as a will.

07:15.340 --> 07:17.683
Court? Nah.

07:17.740 --> 07:19.344
I mean, they might be
a little hurt,

07:23.790 --> 07:26.873
Land may look like dirt,
but, really,

07:26.920 --> 07:29.229
it's just brown money.

07:29.270 --> 07:32.797
I've seen_
some ugly things.

07:32.840 --> 07:34.398
Just keep an eye out.

07:34.450 --> 07:35.747
Be careful.

07:37.280 --> 07:39.145
[ paper rustles ]

07:43.460 --> 07:46.896
This is about
your future... and his.

07:46.940 --> 07:47.838
[ Blue humming ]

07:49.900 --> 07:52.243
Oprah on TV:
I feel the presence of God
when I breathe...

07:52.290 --> 07:54.508
This like service.
It's good.

07:54.560 --> 07:56.505
My life force
is most fulfilled...

07:56.560 --> 07:59.336
I ain't never seen nobody
drinking beer at church.

07:59.390 --> 08:01.164
...when I'm praying.

08:01.210 --> 08:03.258
- Yeah.
- Oprah: I experience
love when...?

08:03.300 --> 08:06.565
[ both laugh ]

08:06.610 --> 08:09.693
[ phone ringing ]

08:09.750 --> 08:11.263
Hush.

08:11.310 --> 08:13.005
- [ phone beeps ]
- Yeah, this Holleood.

08:13.050 --> 08:14.483
Hey, man,
what's happening?

08:14.530 --> 08:17.090
[ chuckles ]
Yeah.

08:17.140 --> 08:19.608
Pretty good having
these last couple days off,
you heard me?

08:22.580 --> 08:23.626
Damn, already?

08:25.850 --> 08:27.715
No, no, that's good.

08:27.760 --> 08:30.103
Oh, yeah, man,
everything fine.

08:30.160 --> 08:33.118
Um... see you
in a couple days.

08:34.730 --> 08:36.595
All right.

08:36.640 --> 08:37.504
[ beeps ]

08:40.470 --> 08:42.552
Sounds like
we on the clock.

08:42.600 --> 08:45.216
Shipping out
in 48 hours.

08:50.480 --> 08:51.697
Well...

08:59.880 --> 09:02.440
Then I think
we'd better get to work.

09:02.490 --> 09:03.536
[ music playing ]

09:03.580 --> 09:05.309
-Hmm?
-[laughs]

09:05.370 --> 09:06.883
- Holleood: Mm.
- [ laughing ]

09:15.510 --> 09:17.375
[ buzzing ]

09:34.740 --> 09:37.652
[ drone buzzing ]

09:42.270 --> 09:43.669
- [ crashes ]
- Blue: Pop!

09:43.710 --> 09:45.189
Blue!

09:47.930 --> 09:50.182
Hey! Blue!

09:53.110 --> 09:55.362
Stand back from there.

09:55.420 --> 09:56.899
- It fell down.
- You okay?

09:56.940 --> 09:58.714
I didn't do
nothing to it.

10:28.100 --> 10:32.230
- [ phone ringing ]
- Woman: Excuse me, sir? Sir!

10:32.280 --> 10:34.054
Sir, Mr. Boudreaux
is not available!

10:34.110 --> 10:37.238
[ chatter, laughter ]

10:40.640 --> 10:42.323
Why don't y'all take
a breather?

10:42.380 --> 10:44.371
This ain't gonna
take that long.

10:49.690 --> 10:50.725
[ clears throat ]

10:50.780 --> 10:52.384
No, like you said,

10:52.430 --> 10:53.909
this ain't gonna
take that long.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.126
How can I help you,
Ralph?

10:57.170 --> 10:58.125
Ralph Angel.

10:59.610 --> 11:00.861
How's Charley?

11:00.920 --> 11:02.399
Y'all's farm
up and running yet?

11:02.440 --> 11:04.908
[ chuckles ]
You know God damn well

11:04.960 --> 11:07.485
exactly how things
going on my farm.

11:07.530 --> 11:09.395
You and your uncle
Sam Landry.

11:09.450 --> 11:11.702
Stay out of my business

11:11.750 --> 11:15.049
and away from our land,
you hear me?

11:15.100 --> 11:17.148
- Stay away?
- Mm-hmm.

11:17.190 --> 11:19.454
I ain't stepped foot
on your farm in months.

11:19.500 --> 11:23.766
Look, I think it's high time
we all let bygones be bygones.

11:23.810 --> 11:26.278
So you ain't gonna be a man
and say what you,

11:26.330 --> 11:28.981
your uncle, and your brother,
and your whole clan is up to?

11:31.120 --> 11:32.428
[ drone clatters ]

11:32.470 --> 11:35.166
But you keep trying
to play me for a fool,

11:35.210 --> 11:37.770
and me and you,

11:37.820 --> 11:40.209
we gonna find out
who the real one is.

11:42.520 --> 11:45.739
You oughta be careful
about your boy playing
outside by himself.

11:45.790 --> 11:48.395
Don't want him
to get hurt.

11:48.440 --> 11:51.785
Go ahead.
Do It.

11:51.840 --> 11:55.662
Be the quickest way
to put you away for
a long while...

11:55.710 --> 11:57.143
convict.

12:04.720 --> 12:05.971
Okay.

12:07.900 --> 12:09.765
Here it is.

12:09.810 --> 12:12.370
You even look
my boy's way...

12:14.030 --> 12:16.590
there ain't no jail
big enough

12:16.640 --> 12:19.905
or bad enough to keep me
from hurting you.

12:21.560 --> 12:23.289
Watch yourself.

12:30.440 --> 12:31.919
[ doorbell rings ]

12:33.360 --> 12:34.486
Hey, Charley.

12:37.320 --> 12:40.278
Micah didn't ask you
to share custody, Davis.

12:41.800 --> 12:43.233
You lied.

12:43.280 --> 12:44.759
No, I didn't.
He said he wanted--

12:44.800 --> 12:46.620
Charley:
To get a burger with you
on the weekends!

12:46.670 --> 12:49.548
That's not the same
as asking you for
joint custody.

12:49.590 --> 12:52.502
- You twisted his words.
- Come on, we're talking
about our son, okay?

12:52.550 --> 12:55.417
You weren't thinking about
our son when you were messing
around with those hookers

12:55.470 --> 12:58.155
or when you
publicly humiliated us.

13:05.340 --> 13:07.820
Come on, Charley,
you know my background, okay?

13:07.870 --> 13:09.565
I didn't have
what you had.

13:09.610 --> 13:11.384
There was
no father figure
in my life,

13:11.440 --> 13:14.432
not until I met you
and then Ernest became
my father, too, okay?

13:14.480 --> 13:17.836
And look, even though Ernest
had Nova and Ralph Angel,

13:17.880 --> 13:19.916
even though
he was with True
and not Lorna,

13:19.970 --> 13:22.700
and even though he lived
in Louisiana and you were
all the way in California,

13:22.750 --> 13:24.354
he was there for you
while you grew up.

13:24.410 --> 13:25.354
You know why?

13:25.410 --> 13:27.571
He had access to you.

13:27.630 --> 13:30.588
He was allowed,
and without drama.

13:30.630 --> 13:33.064
That's one thing
Lorna got right,
and you know it.

13:33.110 --> 13:35.670
I need that.

13:35.720 --> 13:37.278
I need that
if I'm gonna be

13:37.330 --> 13:39.286
what you say you want me
to be for Micah.

13:48.740 --> 13:51.516
You almost convinced me
that you're snncere.

13:51.560 --> 13:54.859
I actually have
to remind myself

13:54.920 --> 13:57.138
who you are
every time you speak.

13:59.220 --> 14:02.781
I'm not sharing
custody.

14:02.840 --> 14:05.092
And if Micah doesn't say
he wants it,

14:05.140 --> 14:06.960
there's no way
you're getting it.

14:07.020 --> 14:09.625
And don't ever
compare yourself
to my father again.

14:09.670 --> 14:12.662
You don't even deserve to_be
In the same sentence as him.

14:12.720 --> 14:15.848
I know you signed my name
to get your loan, Charley.

14:22.250 --> 14:23.899
Yeah.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.987
My lawyer put alerts
on my financials
when you filed.

14:30.470 --> 14:32.643
Just let me be
in my son's life,
Charley.

14:32.690 --> 14:35.818
Or I swear
I'll tell the bank.

14:35.870 --> 14:37.918
See if you get your mill
up and running in time

14:37.960 --> 14:40.656
without that money.

14:40.700 --> 14:44.227
I may have forged your name,
but you were the team pimp.

14:44.270 --> 14:47.922
You wanna go to court?
I'll wear a new suit every day.

14:47.970 --> 14:51.144
Let's see who wins
once It's all out
In the open.

15:00.500 --> 15:03.765
[ both laughing ]

15:03.810 --> 15:06.335
I can't believe
you got me out here
drinking wine coolers.

15:06.380 --> 15:09.508
- [ gasps ]
- This might as well
be a cream soda.

15:09.560 --> 15:11.812
I'm just making best
from what the store had.

15:13.560 --> 15:16.472
_ How old are we
rIght about now? 19?

15:16.520 --> 15:19.296
Well, I feel like I'm 19.

15:19.350 --> 15:21.955
Me and you
against the world.

15:22.000 --> 15:23.342
-Mmm.
- Yeah?

15:23.400 --> 15:25.300
[ music playing ]

15:25.350 --> 15:28.092
Shoot, I don't need
nothing to make me high
except for you anyway.

15:32.230 --> 15:36.883
Well, no matter how young
we feel right about now...

15:38.110 --> 15:40.499
we're both
old enough to know

15:40.540 --> 15:44.158
when a good thing
has to come to an end.

15:44.200 --> 15:46.065
Ah, don't say that.

15:46.110 --> 15:48.328
But you know?

15:48.380 --> 15:51.076
I bet you five months
will go by real fast.

15:58.130 --> 15:59.427
I'm sure it will.

16:04.310 --> 16:05.823
[ music playing ]

16:05.870 --> 16:07.599
Charley:
Hey. What's so urgent?

16:07.660 --> 16:10.561
I don't wanna talk about
this loan thing again,
Ralph Angel.

16:10.620 --> 16:12.872
I would have called Nova
if she was here.

16:12.920 --> 16:16.185
Trust me,
I don't wanna sit_here
talkIng to you neIther.

16:16.230 --> 16:18.186
But you need to know
something.

16:18.230 --> 16:19.709
Landry been messing
with the farm.

16:19.760 --> 16:21.921
What do you mean
"messing with the farm"?

16:21.980 --> 16:23.277
What does that mean?

16:23.330 --> 16:26.015
He been having
drones fly over.

16:26.070 --> 16:28.368
Wait, what?

16:28.420 --> 16:29.842
Since when?

16:29.900 --> 16:31.458
I don't know how long
he been at it.

16:31.510 --> 16:33.023
Blue saw it first,

16:33.070 --> 16:36.369
just flying over
like it wasn't no thing.

16:36.430 --> 16:38.500
The audacity
of these people.

16:38.560 --> 16:40.903
Yeah, pretty damn audacious.

16:40.950 --> 16:43.942
[ chuckles ]
So, I went over
to his office.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.298
You-- why didn't
you call me first?

16:46.350 --> 16:48.432
It's done, Charley.

16:50.870 --> 16:53.304
He was trespassing.
I did what I should've done.

16:53.360 --> 16:55.658
I stepped to him
man to man,

16:55.710 --> 16:58.099
warned him
not to do it again.

16:58.140 --> 16:59.619
Man to man, huh?

17:01.580 --> 17:04.140
[ chuckles ]
I'm afraid to ask
what that reallymeans.

17:04.190 --> 17:07.148
See, this is why I can't
sign those loan papers.

17:07.200 --> 17:08.974
What happens if you make
a decision on your own

17:09.020 --> 17:10.282
that puts all of us
at risk?

17:10.330 --> 17:12.286
See, you just don't
understand, ever.

17:12.330 --> 17:14.503
No, youdon't understand.

17:14.550 --> 17:16.598
Next time there's a problem
with the Landrys,

17:16.640 --> 17:19.029
I need to know
before, not after,

17:19.080 --> 17:20.945
you do something
you don't know
enough about.

17:28.350 --> 17:30.910
[ music playing ]

17:42.490 --> 17:44.355
[ chatter ]

17:47.630 --> 17:49.791
Ms. Nova Bordelon.

